<subSubSection id="C3412BDDFF80FF8EFF4E0EE2FAE62833" pageId="9" pageNumber="255" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE47856FF80FF8EFF4E0EE2FAE62833" blockId="9.[151,1436,1534,1885]" pageId="9" pageNumber="255">
In addition to the new species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B03D5FF80FF8EFDD70EE2FDC12976" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1809" box="[526,629,1535,1560]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Phyllanthaceae" genus="Leptopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Malpighiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="255" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92FA444FF80FF8EFDD70EE2FDC12976" box="[526,629,1535,1560]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="255">Leptopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
described above, the small water strider 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B03D5FF80FF8EFB9A0EE3FB7C2976" authorityName="Kolenati" authorityYear="1857" box="[1091,1224,1534,1560]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Velia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="255" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="affinis">
<emphasis id="B92FA444FF80FF8EFB9A0EE3FB7C2976" box="[1091,1224,1534,1560]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="255">Velia affinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was also collected from two of the caves investigated. The species was previously recorded from 
<collectingCountry id="F34C38C6FF80FF8EFBC70D3EFBFF2953" box="[1054,1099,1571,1597]" name="Iran" pageId="9" pageNumber="255">Iran</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCA05A7FF80FF8EFBA10D3FFADF2952" author="Ghahari, H. &amp; Moulet, P. &amp; Ostovan, H. &amp; Linnavuori, R. E." box="[1144,1387,1570,1596]" pageId="9" pageNumber="255" pagination="301 - 342" refId="ref6592" refString="Ghahari, H., Moulet, P., Ostovan, H. &amp; Linnavuori, R. E. (2013) An annotated catalog of the Iranian Dipsocoromorpha, Enicocephalomorpha, Gerromorpha, Leptopodomorpha and Nepomorpha (Hemiptera: Heteroptera). Zootaxa, 3641 (4), 301 - 342. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3641.4.1" type="journal article" year="2013">
Ghahari 
<emphasis id="B92FA444FF80FF8EFB020D3EFAA12952" box="[1243,1301,1570,1596]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="255">et al.</emphasis>
(2013)
</bibRefCitation>
, but from surface waters. During the course of the current investigations, five females and one male of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B03D5FF80FF8EFB020D5BFAEB290E" authorityName="Kolenati" authorityYear="1857" box="[1243,1375,1606,1632]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Velia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="255" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="affinis">
<emphasis id="B92FA444FF80FF8EFB020D5BFAEB290E" box="[1243,1375,1606,1632]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="255">Velia affinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were collected in the twilight and lighted zones of Dasht-e Shir 2 Cave and Cheshmeh Ta’laou Cave (
<figureCitation id="136064D3FF80FF8EFB1B0D77FAF329EA" box="[1218,1351,1642,1668]" captionStart="FIGURES 11, 12" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1045,1070]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1019]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,181,1020]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 11, 12. Interior views of Chesmeh Ta’alou Cave, Iran, collection locality for Velia affinis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3758321" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3758321/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="255">Figs. 11, 12</figureCitation>
), but in different 
<typeStatus id="54E0C6F4FF80FF8EFF270D92FE8D29C7" box="[254,313,1679,1705]" pageId="9" pageNumber="255">types</typeStatus>
of habitat. In the Dasht-e Shir cave there is a water feature in the lighted zone of cave system which might be fed by underground waters, with the water level here changing in response to variations in seasonal precipitation. Specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B03D5FF80FF8EFE690DCAFDA6299E" authorityName="Kolenati" authorityYear="1857" box="[432,530,1750,1776]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Velia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="255" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="affinis">
<emphasis id="B92FA444FF80FF8EFE690DCAFDA6299E" box="[432,530,1750,1776]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="255">V. affinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were collected from the twilight zone close to the lighted zone. By contrast, the Chesmeh Ta’alou Cave is a channel with a low ceiling (
<figureCitation id="136064D3FF80FF8EFD220DE7FCCB287A" box="[763,895,1786,1812]" captionStart="FIGURES 11, 12" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1045,1070]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1019]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,181,1020]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 11, 12. Interior views of Chesmeh Ta’alou Cave, Iran, collection locality for Velia affinis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3758321" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3758321/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="255">Figs. 11, 12</figureCitation>
), located down in a valley with muddy substrate, and is provided with water from the entrance to the twilight zone. The amount of annual precipitation affects the water level here as well. The specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B03D5FF80FF8EFDA00C5EFD6F2832" authorityName="Kolenati" authorityYear="1857" box="[633,731,1858,1884]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Velia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="255" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="affinis">
<emphasis id="B92FA444FF80FF8EFDA00C5EFD6F2832" box="[633,731,1858,1884]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="255">V. affinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were again collected from the twilight zone of the cave.
</paragraph>
